Start a tmux session:
$ tmux

List tmux sessions:
$ tmux ls

Switch between virtual terminals managed by tmux:

Ctrl-b <#>  where <#> is the terminal number (1, 2, etc.)
Ctrl-b n : switch to next terminal numerically, with wraparound
Ctrl-b p : switch to previous terminal numerically, with wraparound

Detach from tmux session without ending it:
Ctrl-b d

Attach to the last created tmux session:
$ tmux a

Attach to a specified tmux session:
$ tmux a -t <#>   where <#> is a session number as shown by "tmux ls"

Kill last created tmux session:
$ tmux kill-session

Kill a specified tmux session:
$ tmux kill-session <#>   where <#> is a session number as shown by "tmux ls"

Kill all tmux sessions and the tmux server:
$ tmux kill-server

Exit tmux:
$ exit
